name: annexin A10
summary: This gene encodes a member of the annexin family.  Members of this calcium-dependent phospholipid-binding protein family play a role in the regulation of cellular growth and in signal transduction pathways.  The function of this gene has not yet been determined. [provided by RefSeq, Jul 2008].
